Ferrari Enzo

We've updated the Ferrari Enzo information and compared it against the Bugatti Veyron and SSC Ultimate Aero! These are some of the fastest cars in the world!

5/23/2010

Bugatti Veyron Vs. SSC Ultimate Aero

The Bugatti Veyron is arguably the fastest car in the word, with a maximum speed of 253 mph and a 0-to-60 time of 2.5 seconds. The SSC Aero has 1183 horsepower, against the 1001 horsepower of the Bugatti Veyron. This extra horsepower and lighter frame allow the SSC Ultimate Aero to outrun the Bugatti Veyron's top speed. The SSC Aero tops out at 257 mph against the Bugatti Veyron's 253 mph. So which is more important? 0-60 speed or maximum speed? That's for you to decide! Either way, these are both beautiful cars!
